<i>"attempted murder".</i>

767
01:02:41,320 --> 01:02:46,838
<i>Everything before, everything beautiful,</i>
<i>does not exist in the public mind.</i>

768
01:02:46,960 --> 01:02:51,556
<i>No one thinks of how I loved</i>
<i>my children. Look at Cosima.</i>

769
01:02:51,680 --> 01:02:54,717
<i>And Alex, of course. And Ala.</i>

770
01:02:54,840 --> 01:02:57,149
<i>And certainly no one cares about Claus,</i>

771
01:02:57,280 --> 01:03:00,033
<i>the way he was when</i>
<i>I fell in love with him.</i>

772
01:03:00,160 --> 01:03:03,311
<i>When Claus and I first met,</i>
<i>I was married to the dashing young</i>

773
01:03:03,440 --> 01:03:09,117
<i>Prince Alfred Eduard Friederich</i>
<i>Vincenz Martin Maria von Auersberg.</i>

774
01:03:09,240 --> 01:03:14,758
<i>It was 1964, seven years</i>
<i>into my first marriage.</i>

775
01:03:20,200 --> 01:03:25,035
<i>It seems that my first husband,</i>
<i>Alfie, as he was called,</i>

776
01:03:25,160 --> 01:03:29,597
<i>had vowed to be unfaithful</i>
<i>with every pretty girl in Europe.</i>

777
01:03:31,360 --> 01:03:34,591
<i>He was having quite a success.</i>

778
01:03:35,200 --> 01:03:40,115
<i>And so... I was unfaithful with Claus.</i>

779
01:03:50,440 --> 01:03:51,395
Psst.

780
01:03:57,520 --> 01:03:59,909
<i>Wildly unfaithful.</i>

781
01:04:01,200 --> 01:04:03,509
<i>Happy memories.</i>

782
01:04:10,960 --> 01:04:14,919
<i>But it's not the passion</i>
<i>I remember most.</i>

783
01:04:15,040 --> 01:04:17,235
<i>It's the tenderness.</i>

784
01:04:22,120 --> 01:04:24,475
Good God, what's that?

785
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:27,034
Just one of Frank's pets.

786
01:04:31,080 --> 01:04:33,036
Oh, my God.

787
01:04:47,600 --> 01:04:48,589
Come on, silly.

788
01:04:48,720 --> 01:04:52,110
<i>I never liked people much, not as a rule.</i>

789
01:04:53,560 --> 01:04:56,313
<i>But Claus was somehow different.</i>

790
01:04:58,360 --> 01:05:00,749
<i>Not a normal person, I guess.</i>

791
01:05:04,640 --> 01:05:08,269
It's all right. Do it again.
Give him some more.

792
01:05:20,200 --> 01:05:23,351
<i>One of those things you never forget.</i>

793
01:05:24,480 --> 01:05:30,271
<i>Of course, now he lives</i>
<i>in my apartment, my bedroom,</i>

794
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:32,550
<i>my bed.</i>

795
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:38,550
<i>Cold, isn't it? Cold and brutish,</i>
<i>and the way of the world.</i>

796
01:05:39,560 --> 01:05:43,075
<i>Looking at him now,</i>
<i>the issue seems simple.</i>

797
01:05:43,200 --> 01:05:45,156
<i>Is he the devil?</i>

798
01:05:45,280 --> 01:05:48,716
<i>If so, can the devil get justice?</i>

799
01:05:49,680 --> 01:05:56,119
<i>And all this legal activity...</i>
<i>is it in Satan's service?</i>

800
01:05:56,240 --> 01:05:58,435
"Sunny von Bulow was totally vulnerable

801
